    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.Map<java.lang.String,Symbol<?>>

    public class DatasetSchema
extends SymbolTable
    A DatasetSchema is a SymbolTable that represents the schema for a DatasetRecord. Each symbol in a DatasetSchema represents an attribute of the record

      • canExtend

        public static java.lang.String canExtend(DatasetSchema schema,
                         java.util.List<Symbol<?>> newAttributes)
        Check if a set of attributes can be added to a dataset without duplication in the Schema, return null if no issues are found. The method checks both duplication with the existing schema and duplicate name in the list of attributes to be added. If passed a null or empty list of attributes, the method will warn in the logs but return true. A detailed error message is returned if issues are found.
        Parameters:
        schema - the schema to extend
        newAttributes - the List of new attributes as Symbol
        Returns:
        either a String with detailed error messages about all conflicting new attributes, or null if there are none.
